        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10285",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "http:\/\/www.postgresql.org\/docs\/8.1\/interactive\/functions-sequence.html\n\nThere are two functions available, lastval(), and currval().\n\nAll the other existing adapters, except mssql, rely on the behavior described by lastval() -obviously not the same code\/implementation, but neverytheless, the same behavior.  In examining PHP5's PDO implementation for PDO::lastInsertId, in pgsql_driver.c:pdo_pgsql_last_insert_id(), we see the use of CURRVAL(), *not* LASTVAL().  Thus, unlike some of the other PDO drivers, a correct sequence name must be supplied (not optional) to PDO::lastInsertId().\n\nSince the proposed change in this issue's description alters a generic class (Zend_Db_Table) with code specific only to PgSQL, we can not apply the change as described to Zend_Db_Table.  Instead, every adapter must be supplied enough information to construct a sequence name (if needed) according to the format required for that adapter's DB.\n\nPlease see the FishEye link above for changeset information.\n\nHelp solicited for unit tests.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-04T17:00:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-04T17:00:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10429",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "0.1.5 released",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-11T11:54:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-11T11:54:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10617",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=luddic",
                        "name": "luddic",
                        "displayName": "Ludovic Levesque",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Current code is incompatible with sequence name not automatically generated.\n\nIndex: library\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Pdo\/Pgsql.php\n===================================================================\n--- library\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Pdo\/Pgsql.php       (revision 923)\n+++ library\/Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Pdo\/Pgsql.php       (working copy)\n@@ -146,13 +146,17 @@\n     \/**\n      * Gets the last inserted ID.\n      *\n-     * @param  string $tableName   table or sequence name needed for some PDO drivers\n+     * @param  string $tableName   table or sequence name (if primaryKey is null) needed for some PDO drivers\n      * @param  string $primaryKey  primary key in $tableName need for some PDO drivers\n      * @return integer\n      *\/\n     public function lastInsertId($tableName = null, $primaryKey = null)\n     {\n         $this->_connect();\n-        return $this->_connection->lastInsertId($tableName .'_'. $primaryKey .'_seq');\n+        if (is_null($primaryKey)) {\n+            return $this->_connection->lastInsertId($tableName);\n+        } else {\n+            return $this->_connection->lastInsertId($tableName .'_'. $primaryKey .'_seq');\n+        }\n     }\n }\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=luddic",
                        "name": "luddic",
                        "displayName": "Ludovic Levesque",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-27T06:10:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-27T06:10:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10619",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ludovic Levesque supplied an example use case where the issue still occurs.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
